# Worktree-discipline pack — installed from the livespec-dev-tooling package
# (the single canonical source) via `just install-worktree-pack` / bootstrap,
# NOT tracked here. The from-package installer writes byte-identical copies
# into dev-tooling/ at bootstrap, mirroring how the commit-refuse hooks are
# installed into the untracked .git/hooks/ dir. The pack is four files: the
# two executable shell scripts plus the `worktree.just` and
# `branch-protection.just` recipe fragments the root justfile `import?`s. The
# per-ecosystem dev-tooling/worktree-hydrate.sh stub stays TRACKED (it is not
# part of the package pack); the rest of dev-tooling/ (e.g.
# ensure-rust-quality-tools.sh) is tracked too — these anchored globs ignore
# ONLY the four pack files.
/dev-tooling/worktree-lib.sh
/dev-tooling/branch-protection.sh
/dev-tooling/worktree.just
/dev-tooling/branch-protection.just
